The paper deals with the problem of serving traffic over a multi-channel communication system with time-varying channel states and unknown statistics. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as it involves coding and channel capacity. It also falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with multi-channel networks. The paper proposes an index-based policy for dynamic channel allocation, which involves learning and decision-making, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of optimizing the performance of the system, which is related to control and optimization (cs.SY).
